text: Ilijana Dugandžić (born 17 April 1981) is a Croatian national volleyball player. She played at the 2005 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2007 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2011 Women's European Volleyball Championship, and 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for Mladost Zagreb and Igtisadchi Baku. == References == Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:Croatian volleyball players
